<div id="masthead"><h1 class="sub">Rehabilitation Services</h1><div id="textsize"><a href="#" id="regular"><img src="/images/site/text-regular.gif" border="0" alt="Text Size - Regular" title="Text Size - Regular" width="51" hieght="30"  /></a><a href="#" id="large"><img src="/images/site/text-large.gif" border="0" alt="Text Size - Large" title="Text Size - Large" width="51" hieght="30"  /></a></div></div>
<div id="side-content">
	
	
	
	<h2>Rehabilitation Therapy to Get You Back on Track</h2>					
						<div class="floatleftcopy">
			
				<img src="/images/made/images/uploads/rehab_280_420_100.jpg" alt="" width="280" height="420" border="0" alt="Physical therapy. " title="Physical therapy. " /><br /><div class="caption" style="width: 280px">Short- and long-term rehabilitation therapy.</div>			
			</div>
					
				
	<p>
	Our results tell the story. People who receive rehabilitation therapy at Wilson&rsquo;s Transitional Care Unit following a hospitalization see sharp improvements in many of the ways doctors measure a good recovery. Our unwavering focus is on creating a setting where you can regain strength and resume your normal living arrangements as quickly as possible, whether you are recovering from surgery, an illness or an injury.</p>
<p>
	Wilson Health Care Center offers&nbsp;innovations in therapy you won&#39;t find anywhere else. The OmniVR is a virtual rehabilitation system that uses an advanced 3D camera and specialized software to track a patient&#39;s precise movements and allow them to interact in a virtual world. Virtual rehab treatment outcomes can equal or even exceed those achieved with traditional therapeutic exercise alone. Asbury is the only community in&nbsp;Maryland with this equipment.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Plus, unlike many therapy providers, Wilson provides rehabilitation services seven days a week, so your progress isn&rsquo;t interrupted on weekends. Just as important, our team of rehabilitation therapists works closely with your personal physician to promote a good recovery.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Wilson offers the following therapies</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		Physical therapy - To help you rebuild strength and balance</li>
	<li>
		Occupational therapy - To improve your ability to manage everyday tasks</li>
	<li>
		Speech/language therapy - To help you improve speech and swallowing abilities</li>
</ul>

	
	<br clear="all" />
		<div class="callout">
	<h2>
	Whether you&rsquo;re scheduling a knee replacement or recovering from emergency surgery or an illness, it can be daunting to figure out all of the arrangements for your follow-up care.</h2>
<p>
	You do have a choice. When you choose Wilson, a clinical liaison will visit you in the hospital before your discharge and help you sort out all of the details. Call Cynthia Perez at (301) 216-4136 either when you&rsquo;re planning for a surgery or if you have an unexpected illness and hospital stay.</p>

	</div>
		
		
		
		
	
		<h2>File Download</h2>
	
	<p><a href="/images/uploads/pdf/Admission_sheet-2_pgs.pdf" target="_blank">Wilson Heath Care Center Admissions Form</a></p>
	
		
		
	
